Simple command examples: 

# Will run on all php-files in the folder and any subdirectories
find . -name '*.php' -exec sh fixmethod "{}" \; > git.diff

# Will do the same, but not look in the folders cache and hooks
find . -type d \( -path ./cache -o -path ./hooks \) -prune -o -name '*.php' -exec sh fixmethod "{}" \; > git.diff
